main event: An unidentified object was observed in Holbrook, Arizona on September 6, 1953, emitting a blue flame and moving in a northeast to southwest course.
interesting points: The observation lasted 40-45 seconds., The object was described as elongated with a tail and had a fluorescent glow., It was reported at an altitude of approximately 15,000 to 23,000 feet and moving at an estimated speed of over 500 mph., The sighting was confirmed by multiple observers, including military personnel., The conclusion drawn from the report was that the object could be a rocket or fireball.
sighted object: one elongated object emitting a blue flame
